President Obama met with African American civil rights and faith leaders to discuss the Administration's priorities, including criminal justice, education, healthcare, and economic development. The President highlighted the upcoming release of a report by the Task Force on 21st Century Policing and emphasized the need for bipartisan efforts to reform the criminal justice system. He also mentioned the progress made by the My Brother's Keeper Initiative and discussed the importance of strengthening voting laws. The leaders in attendance agreed to continue outreach to their communities and work with the Administration on implementing its initiatives.